    "steps": [
      "Rinse the eggplant and pat dry. Apply a thin layer of oil over the surface.",
      "Roast the eggplant over an open flame, turning every 2-3 minutes to ensure even cooking. Alternatively, grill or roast in the oven, though the smoky flavor may be less pronounced.",
      "Once fully cooked and tender, immerse the roasted eggplant in a bowl of water to cool.",
      "Peel off the charred skin and finely chop or mash the eggplant pulp.",
      "In a pan, heat oil and sauté the chopped onions and garlic until translucent.",
      "Add the chopped green chili and cook for an additional minute.",
      "Incorporate the chopped tomatoes and cook until the oil separates from the mixture.",
      "Stir in the red chili powder and mix well.",
      "Add the mashed eggplant and combine thoroughly with the onion-tomato mixture.",
      "Season with salt and cook for another 4-5 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld.",
      "Garnish with chopped coriander leaves.",
      "Serve hot with phulkas, rotis, chapatis, or rice.",
